    • onLogin

      public void onLogin​(LoginResponse message)
      Manages the login response

      ed on the LoginResponse outcome

      • Type.OK: login successful, the user is in the waiting room and asked to create/join a lobby
      • Type.SERVER_FULL: the server has exceeded its maximum capacity, won't accept new connections
      • Type.INVALID_NAME: the username is already taken or forbidden
      At this stage, the method also tries to save the address+username combo in a file, for quick access on the next login.
      Specified by:
      onLogin in interface ClientMessageManagerVisitor
      Parameters:
      message - the message to handle
